caption.text:
In less than a month my good friend, Ashley Callingbull, #MissUniverseCanada2024, will crown her successor in Windsor, Ontario. As excited as I am to see who the next #Canadian Queen will be, it’s all so bittersweet! I’m sad to see her reign end, but I know that she has so much more coming up, beyond the pageant stage. After many conversations, training sessions, and Ashley being the go-getter she is, it was amazing to see her hardwork, resilience and dream of becoming #MissUniverseCanada come to fruition ❤️ She made Canada proud by placing in the Top 12 at #MissUniverse 2024 in Mexico City! @ashleycallingbull thank you for taking me along for the ride! You have made history by being the first #Indigenous woman to represent Canada on the Miss Universe stage, and have shattered those glass ceilings for anyone who has hopes and dreams to do the same! 

I’ve always appreciated the start of our friendship since that day in 2012 at the Pink Elephant Restaurant in Vancouver (we hit it off from the get go) - but to remain friends after all this time, and support you on your journey has meant so much! ❤️ Super proud of everything you’ve overcome and have accomplished! 

Xo, Andrew of #thepageantspotlight
